---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '5 May 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Family Friendly UK"
  description="How Family Friendly UK collects, uses, and protects your personal data, in line with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span aria-current="page">Privacy Policy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal-prose">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Family Friendly UK ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses,
        and protects your personal information when you use our website. We're committed to
        handling your data in line with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and
        the Data Protection Act 2018.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Family Friendly UK is a directory of family-friendly restaurants across the UK. We are
        the data controller for any personal data you provide through this site. If you have any
        questions about this policy or how your data is handled, please contact us through our
        <a href="/suggest">contact form</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect the following information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you submit</strong> — when you suggest a restaurant, sign up to
          our newsletter, or contact us, we collect the details you provide such as your name,
          email address, and any message you send.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage information</strong> — like most websites, we collect basic information
          about how visitors use the site, such as pages viewed and approximate location, to
          help us improve the service.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Location data</strong> — if you use the "Near me" feature, your browser will
          ask for permission to share your location. This is used only to centre the map; it's
          not stored or shared.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use your data</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to restaurant suggestions and other enquiries</li>
        <li>Send our newsletter (only if you've signed up — you can unsubscribe at any time)</li>
        <li>Understand how the site is used, so we can make it better</li>
        <li>Comply with our legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Our lawful bases for processing under UK GDPR are: your consent (e.g. newsletter
        sign-up), the performance of a service you've requested (e.g. responding to a
        suggestion), and our legitimate interests (e.g. improving the site).
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use a small number of cookies to make the site work and to understand how it's used:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Essential cookies</strong> — required for core functionality such as
          remembering your preferences. These don't need consent.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — help us count visitors and see which pages are
          popular, in aggregate. We don't use these to identify individuals.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Mapbox</strong> — our interactive map is provided by Mapbox, which may set
          cookies for performance and crash reporting. See the
          <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/legal/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Mapbox privacy notice</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can control cookies through your browser settings. Blocking cookies may affect how
        the site works.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing your data</h2>
      <p>
        We don't sell your personal data. We share it only with trusted service providers
        needed to run the site (such as our newsletter provider and our hosting platform), and
        only to the extent needed for them to provide their service. These providers act under
        contract and are themselves obliged to protect your data.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal data only as long as we need it for the purposes set out above. Email
        addresses on our newsletter list are kept until you unsubscribe. Suggestions and
        enquiries are kept for up to two years after we've replied.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ask for a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Ask us to correct data that's inaccurate</li>
        <li>Ask us to delete your data ("right to erasure")</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict our processing of your data</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time, where consent is the basis for processing</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Information Commissioner's Office</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us through the <a href="/suggest">contact form</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This site is intended for use by adults planning meals out with their families. We
        don't knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this
        page tells you when it was last changed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal-prose {
  max-width: 760px;
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--text);
  padding: 24px 24px 64px;
}
.legal-prose h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--green);
  margin: 36px 0 12px;
}
.legal-prose p { margin-bottom: 14px; color: var(--text-muted); }
.legal-prose ul {
  margin: 4px 0 18px 0;
  padding-left: 20px;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}
.legal-prose li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.legal-prose a { color: var(--green); text-decoration: underline; }
.legal-prose a:hover { color: var(--terracotta); }
</style>
